The paper discusses the differences between OT and CRDT in building co-editing systems, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). It also examines the role of building working co-editors in OT and CRDT research, which relates to Software Engineering (cs.SE). The paper evaluates CRDT-based co-editors in relation to published CRDT solutions, which falls under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the evolution of co-editors from research vehicles to real-world applications, which relates to Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Computer Communication and Networks (cs.CC).
